summary: This is an email chain from September 2021 among FBI personnel discussing the search for miscellaneous notes, particularly from a July 2019 search of Jeffrey Epstein's property. The chain reveals an agent found one page of notes from an interview with a housekeeper during that search and is inquiring whether to file a formal report (302) or just upload the notes.

events.title: Original Epstein Search
events.description: FBI search of Jeffrey Epstein's property, during which an agent interviewed a housekeeper and took notes.

keyFacts: An FBI agent found one page of handwritten notes from an interview with a housekeeper during the July 2019 search of Jeffrey Epstein's property.
The agent did not write a formal FBI 302 report at the time and is seeking guidance on whether to create one now or simply upload the notes.

The email chain indicates an ongoing effort in September 2021 to locate and consolidate all miscellaneous notes from the Epstein investigation, specifically from the New York and US Virgin Islands searches.
The correspondence is internal FBI communication, highlighting post-investigation document management procedures.
